============================================================
  ECONOMICS
============================================================

Concept:    Moral Hazard
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Entity takes more risk when not bearing full consequences
Formula:    Conceptual
Economist:  Adam Smith/Pauly
Example:    Banks took excessive risks knowing government would bail them out 2008

Concept:    Elasticity
Category:   Microeconomics
Definition: Responsiveness of demand to price change
Formula:    PED = %dQd / %dP
Economist:  Alfred Marshall
Example:    Gasoline demand inelastic; luxury goods elastic

Concept:    Comparative Advantage
Category:   International Trade
Definition: Countries gain by specializing in what they produce most efficiently
Formula:    Compare opportunity cost ratios
Economist:  David Ricardo
Example:    China makes electronics cheaply; USA makes pharma cheaply; both gain trading

============================================================
  FAMOUS PEOPLE
============================================================

Name:          Mahatma Gandhi
Lived:         1869 - 1948
Nationality:   Indian
Field:         Politics
Known For:     Non-violent independence movement
Contribution:  Led India to independence; satyagraha philosophy; influenced MLK and Mandela
Quote:         "Be the change you wish to see in the world."

Name:          Leonardo da Vinci
Lived:         1452 - 1519
Nationality:   Italian
Field:         Art/Science
Known For:     Mona Lisa, anatomy
Contribution:  Renaissance polymath; Mona Lisa; anatomical drawings; flying machine designs
Quote:         "Learning never exhausts the mind."

Name:          Florence Nightingale
Lived:         1820 - 1910
Nationality:   English
Field:         Medicine
Known For:     Modern nursing
Contribution:  Founded modern nursing; used statistics; reduced Crimean War mortality 40% to 2%
Quote:         "I attribute my success to this: I never gave or took any excuse."

